<sect1> What documentation is available for Linux?
<p>
A lot of information about the Linux operating system is available;
large parts of this information are freetexts, like this one.  The
documents listed here are not specific to Debian.
See section <ref id="WhatIsDebian" name="What is Debian GNU/Linux?"> for
Debian GNU/Linux specific documentation.

<sect2> The Linux FAQ
<p>
The Linux FAQ by Ian Jackson, is posted regularly in the Usenet group
<htmlurl url="news:comp.os.linux.announce"
     name="comp.os.linux.announce">.
Like many FAQs it is also available via anonymous FTP at
<url url="ftp://rtfm.mit.edu/pub/usenet/news.answers/linux/faq/">
and via WWW at
<url url="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/users/iwj10/linux-faq/">.

<sect2> The HOWTO's and other Linux documentation
<p>
The
<htmlurl url="http://sunsite.unc.edu/LDP/" name="Home Page of the Linux
Documentation Project> contains pointers to many other useful references.
This site is mirrored around the world; a list of mirrors is given at
<url url="http://sunsite.unc.edu/LDP/hmirrors.html">.

Documents included in the LDP include the famous
<htmlurl url="http://sunsite.unc.edu/LDP/HOWTO/HOWTO-INDEX-3.html"
name="HOWTO"> files, which are compilations of information pertaining to
specific aspects of Linux. HOWTOs cover such things as: Networking, Mail,
News, and UUCP.  Among these are the
<htmlurl url="http://sunsite.unc.edu/LDP/HOWTO/INFO-SHEET.html"
	name="INFO-SHEET"> which gives technical aspects of the GNU/Linux
system, and the
<htmlurl url="http://sunsite.unc.edu/LDP/HOWTO/META-FAQ.html" name="META-FAQ">
which provides other information resources.

See also the
<htmlurl url="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/users/iwj10/linux-faq/"
	name="Linux FAQ">
for additional availability information.

<sect2> Books of the Linux Documentation Project.
<p>
There are several books made by the Linux Documentation Project,
such as a System Administrator's Manual and a Kernel Hackers' Guide.
The full set of book in the LDP is available in several formats online at
<url url="ftp://sunsite.unc.edu/pub/Linux/docs/LDP/">
or one of the sunsite mirrors mentioned above.
These books are now searchable, using
<url url="http://linuxwww.db.erau.edu/Harvest/brokers/linuxwww/">.


<sect1> E-Mail lists
<p>
There are many e-mail lists available for Linux.  Most are specific to
a particular aspect of Linux, others are more general.  The lists are
served by
<htmlurl url="mailto:Majordomo@vger.rutgers.edu"
	name="Majordomo@vger.rutgers.edu">.
Send a message with the word "help" in the body to learn how to
subscribe/unsubscribe from any of the lists.

